    "body": "### Problem\n\nExecuting `:echo expand('%')` without `:p` in the file having LSP diagnostics shows the absolute path. This issue occurs in the file opened after LSP is launched and does not occur in the file opened first. I notice it occurs with lua-language-server or rust-analyzer, but it may occur with other LSPs.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n1. `touch empty.lua .editorconfig`\r\n2. `echo 'global_var = 1' > diagnostic.lua`\r\n3. `nvim -u minimal.lua`\r\n4. `:e empty.lua` and wait for LSP to launch completely\r\n5. `:e diagnostic.lua`\r\n6. `:echo expand('%')`\r\n\r\n`minimal.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal pattern = 'lua'\r\nlocal cmd = { 'lua-language-server' }\r\nlocal root_markers = { '.git', '.editorconfig' }\r\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\r\n  pattern = pattern,\r\n  callback = function(args)\r\n    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil\r\n    vim.lsp.start({\r\n      name = 'bugged-ls',\r\n      cmd = cmd,\r\n      root_dir = root_dir,\r\n      settings = settings\r\n    })\r\n\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should return the relative path.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2563+g1da0f3494\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nlua-language-server 3.7.4, rust-analyzer 2024-03-04\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux on WSL\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
